lications/ixpdir/?show_active_only=0&sort=traffic&order=desc Packet Clearing House - Internet Exchange Directory] (automatically updated daily list)\n*[http://www.telegeography.com/products/internet-exchange-directory/ TeleGeography: The Internet Exchange Points Directory]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110717191004/https://www.euro-ix.net/member/m/about/memberlist Euro-IX Member IXPs]\n*[http://lookinglass.org/wix.php LookinGlass.Org: IXP's with BGP LG service in the World]\n\n[[Category:Internet exchange points| ]]\n[[Category:Routing]]\n[[Category:Internet-related lists|exchange points]]\n\n[[de:Internet-Knoten#Tabelle internationaler Internet-Knoten (GIX) (nach Traffic sortiert)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{See also |List of Internet exchange points}}\nThis is a '''list of [[Internet exchange point]]s by size''', measured by peak data rate ([[throughput]]), with additional data on location, establishment and average throughput.\n\nGenerally only exchanges with more than ten [[gigabit per second|gigabits per second]] peak throughput have been taken into consideration. The numbers in the list represent switched traffic only (no private interconnects) and are rounded to whole gigabits. Take into consideration that traffic on each exchange point can change quickly, and be seasonal.\n\nThis list is not exhaustive, as it includes only exchanges willing to make traffic data public on their website. Particularly data of IXPs from the [[United States]] and [[China]] is hard to come by. Examples of large peering points without public data are [[NAP of the Americas]] or [[PacketExchange]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" <!-- style=\"text-align:right\" -->\n|- style=\"background:#ececec;\"\n! Short name\n! Name\n! City\n! Country\n! Established\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Members\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Maximum [[throughput]] ([[Gigabit|Gbit]]/[[second|s]])\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Average throughput (Gbit/s)\n! Va