ring\n| [[Robert Cummings]]\n| and Producer\n|-\n| 1949\n| ''[[Samson and Delilah (1949 film)|Samson and Delilah]]''\n| [[Delilah]]\n| [[Victor Mature]]\n| Her first film in [[Technicolor]]\n|-\n| 1950\n| ''[[A Lady Without Passport]]''\n| Marianne Lorress\n| [[John Hodiak]]\n|\n|-\n| 1950\n| ''[[Copper Canyon (film)|Copper Canyon]]''\n| Lisa Roselle\n| [[Ray Milland]]\n|\n|-\n| 1951\n| ''[[My Favorite Spy]]''\n| Lily Dalbray\n| [[Bob Hope]]\n|\n|-\n| 1954\n| ''[[Loves of Three Queens]]''\n| [[Helen of Troy]],<br />[[Jos\u00e9phine de Beauharnais]],<br />[[Genevieve of Brabant]]\n| [[Massimo Serato]],<br />[[Cesare Danova]]\n| Original title: ''L'amante di Paride''\n|-\n| 1957\n| ''[[The Story of Mankind (film)|The Story of Mankind]]''\n| Joan of Arc\n| [[Ronald Colman]]\n|\n|-\n| 1958\n| ''[[The Female Animal]]''\n| Vanessa Windsor\n| [[George Nader]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Series !! Episode\n|-\n| 1957 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || \"Proud Woman\"{{sfn|Barton|2010|p=198}}\n|}\n\n==Radio appearances==\nHedy Lamarr starred in the following [[radio dramas]]:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Program !! Episode\n|-\n| 1941 || ''[[Lux Radio Theatre]]'' || \"[[Algiers (film)|Algiers]]\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Lux Radio Theatre: Algiers (July 7, 1941) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mHMHa4v8i9g |website=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=June 23, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1941 || ''[[Lux Radio Theatre]]'' || \"[[The Bride Came C.O.D.]]\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Lux Radio Theatre: The Bride Came C.O.D. (December 29, 1941) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DMwEJyj9juM |website=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=June 23, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1942 || ''[[The Screen Guild Theater]]'' || \"[[Too Many Husbands]]\"<ref name=\"shearer\" />\n|-\n| 1942 || ''[[Lux Radio Theatre]]'' || \"[[H. M. Pulham, Esq.]]\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Lux Radio Theatre: H.M. Pulham, Esq. (July 13, 1942) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pj4JBdR4Bm8 |webs